  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I created a `find` util function that uses the native `find` method if available, otherwise an implementation with `filter`.\r\n\r\nI chose to keep the native one when available because it's optimized to return once the item is found (it doesn't go through all items).\r\n\r\nIf you're concerned about the `reduce` implementation which goes through all the items, we can refactor it with a basic loop.\r\n\r\nOnce this is merged, we can remove the `find` mention in the Browser support section of the documentation.",
    "created_at": "2019-04-24T14:54:18Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/3706#issuecomment-486276634",
    "id": 486276634,
